#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:6
msgid "Bendy Bones"
msgstr "Bendy Bones 软骨骼"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:8
msgid ""
"Bendy Bones (B-Bones) are an easy way to replace long chains of many "
"small rigid bones. A common use case for curve bones is to model spine "
"columns or facial bones."
msgstr "Bendy Bones（B-Bones）是一种简单的方法取代许多小型刚性骨骼长链的方法。弯曲骨骼的常见用于脊柱模型或面部骨骼。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:13
msgid "Technical Details"
msgstr "Technical Details 技术细节"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:15
msgid ""
"Blender treats the bone as a section of a Bézier curve passing through "
"the bones' joints. Each *Segments* will bend and roll the  to follow this"
" invisible curve representing a tessellated point of the Bézier curve. "
"The control points at each end of the curve are the endpoints of the "
"bone. The shape of the B-Bones can be controlled using a series of "
"properties or indirectly through the neighboring bones (i.e. first child "
"and parent). The properties construct handles on either end of the bone "
"to control the curvature."
msgstr ""
"Blender将骨骼看成通过骨骼关节的贝塞尔曲线的一部分. 每个*段数* "
"将弯曲并滚动以遵循这无形贝塞尔曲线代表此的曲线细分点。曲线两端的控制点是骨骼的端点。 "
"样条骨（B-bones）的形状可以是受控制使用一系列的属性或间接邻近的骨骼(即第一个子级和父级). 骨骼的两端的特征构成手柄以控制曲率。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:25
msgid ""
"When using the B-bone as a constraint target :ref:`ui-data-id` offers an "
"option to follow the curvature."
msgstr "当使用 B-bone 作为约束目标 :ref:`ui-data-id` 提供跟随曲线的选项。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:29
msgid ""
"However, if the bone is used as a target rather than to deform geometry, "
"the roll is not taken in account."
msgstr "然而，如果骨骼用作目标，而不是使几何体变形，则不考虑滚动。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:34
msgid "Display"
msgstr "Display 显示"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:36
msgid "You can see these segments only if bones are visualized as *B-bones*."
msgstr "只有骨骼可视化模式为 *样条骨（B-bones）* 才能看到这些段数。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:38
msgid ""
"When not visualized as *B-Bone* s, bones are always shown as rigid "
"sticks, even though the bone segments are still present and effective. "
"This means that even in e.g. *Octahedron* visualization, if some bones in"
" a chain have several segments, they will nonetheless smoothly deform "
"their geometry..."
msgstr ""
"当显示方式不是 *样条骨（B-bones）* 时, 骨骼总是显示为刚性棍形，即使骨骼段数仍然存在并且有效。 这意味着即使在例如 *八面体* "
"可视化的显示方式，如果链中的一些骨头有几段， 他们仍然会使他们的几何体平滑变形..."

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:46
msgid "Rest Pose"
msgstr "Rest Pose 重置姿势"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:48
msgid ""
"The initial shape of a B-Bone can be defined in Edit Mode as a rest pose "
"of that bone. This is useful for curved facial features like curved "
"eyebrows or mouths."
msgstr "样条骨（B-bones）的初始形状可以在编辑模式中定义为该骨骼的重置姿势。这对弯曲的面部特征（如弯曲的眉毛或嘴巴）很有用。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:51
msgid ""
"B-Bones have two sets of the Bendy Bone properties -- one for Edit mode "
"(i.e. the Rest Pose/Base Rig) and another for Pose Mode -- adding "
"together their values to get the final transforms."
msgstr ""
"样条骨（B-bones）有两套Bendy Bone（软骨骼、弯曲骨骼）属性 - 一个用于编辑模式（即重置姿势/基础绑定Base "
"Rig），另一个用于姿势模式 - 将它们的值相加，以获得最终的变换。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:56
#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:174
msgid "Example"
msgstr "Example 示例"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:65
msgid "The OLD B-Bones, in Edit Mode. ToDo."
msgstr "编辑模式的OLD 样条骨。 ToDo."

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:70
msgid ""
"The Bézier curve superposed to the chain, with its handles placed at "
"bones' joints."
msgstr "贝塞尔曲线叠加在链上，其手柄放置在骨骼的两端。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:77
msgid "The same armature in Object Mode."
msgstr "相同的骨架在物体模式。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:81
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-rig-bone-intro-bbone` we connected three bones, each "
"one made of five segments."
msgstr "在图 :ref:`fig-rig-bone-intro-bbone` 我们连接了三个骨骼，每个骨骼由五段组成。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:84
msgid ""
"Look at Fig. :ref:`fig-rig-bone-intro-same`, we can see how the bones' "
"segments smoothly \"blend\" into each other, even for roll."
msgstr "看图。 :ref:`fig-rig-bone-intro-same` ，我们可以看到骨骼的细分如何平滑地“融合”到彼此，即使是产生了滚动。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:89
msgid ""
"An armature in Pose Mode, B-Bone visualization: Bone.003 has one segment,"
" Bone.004 has four, and Bone.005 has sixteen."
msgstr "骨骼在姿态模式下，骨骼可视化： Bone.003有一段，Bone.004有四段，Bone.005有十六段。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:94
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Options 选项"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:97
msgid "Segments"
msgstr "Segments 段数"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:99
msgid ""
"The *Segments* number button allows you to set the number of segments, "
"which the given bone is subdivided into. Segments are small, rigid linked"
" child bones that interpolate between the root and the tip. The higher "
"this setting, the smoother \"bends\" the bone, but the heavier the pose "
"calculations..."
msgstr ""
"*段数（Segments）* "
"数字按钮允许你设置给定的骨骼被细分的段数。段数是在首端和尾端之间插入的小的，刚性的相连的子骨骼。这个设置越高，骨骼越平滑“弯曲”，但姿势计算负担越重..."

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:105
msgid "Curve XY Offsets"
msgstr "Curve XY Offsets  曲线XY偏移"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:107
msgid ""
"Applies an offsets the curve handle positions on the plane perpendicular "
"to the bone's primary (Y) axis. As a result, the handle moves per-axis "
"(XY) further from its original location, causing the curve to bend."
msgstr "在垂直于骨骼的主（Y）轴的平面上施加曲线柄位置的偏移量。结果，手柄从原始位置每个轴向 (XY)进一步移动，使得曲线弯曲。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:112
msgid "Roll"
msgstr "Roll 扭转"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:116
msgid "Roll In, Out"
msgstr "Roll In, Out 扭转输入， 扭转输出"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:115
msgid ""
"The roll value  (or twisting around the main Y axis of the bone) is "
"interpolated per-segment, between the start and end roll values. It is "
"applied as a rotational offsets on top of the previous rotation."
msgstr "扭转值  (或围绕骨骼的主Y轴扭转)在每个段内插入起始和终止之间的扭转值。它应用旋转偏移给先前旋转的顶部。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:120
msgid "Inherit End Roll"
msgstr "Inherit End Roll  继承尾端扭转"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:119
msgid "ToDo."
msgstr "ToDo."

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:123
msgid "Scale"
msgstr "Scale 缩放"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:128
msgid "Scale In, Out"
msgstr "Scale In, Out 缩放输入，缩放输出"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:126
msgid ""
"Scaling factor that adjusts the thickness of each segment for X and Z "
"axes only, i.e. length is not affected. Similar to *Roll* it is "
"interpolated per-segment."
msgstr "调整X和Z轴每个段的厚度的比例因子，即长度不受影响。与 *Roll（扭转）* 类似，只是它是每段内插的扭转。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:131
msgid "Easing"
msgstr "Easing"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:139
msgid "Ease In, Out"
msgstr "Ease In, Out"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:134
msgid ""
"The *Ease In/Out* number buttons, change the \"length\" of the "
":ref:`\"auto\" <curve-handle-type-auto>` Bézier handle to control the "
"\"root handle\" and \"tip handle\" of the bone, respectively."
msgstr ""
"*Ease In/Out* 数字按钮,改变“长度” :ref:`\"auto\" <curve-handle-type-auto>` "
"贝塞尔曲线手柄分别控制骨的“首端手柄”和“尾端手柄”。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:137
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"These values are proportional to the default length, which of course "
"automatically varies depending on bone length, angle with the reference "
"handle, and so on."
msgstr "这些值与默认长度成正比，当然这取决于骨骼长度，手柄参考角度等自动变化的过程。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:141
msgid "Ease In/Out settings example, with a materialized Bézier curve."
msgstr "Ease In/Out设置示例，具有实例化的贝塞尔曲线。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:146
msgid "Look at Bone.004: it has the default In and Out values (1.0)."
msgstr "看看Bone.004：它有默认的In和Out值（1.0）。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:151
msgid "Bone.004 with In at 2.0, and Out at 0.0."
msgstr "Bone.004，In为2.0，Out为0.0。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:155
msgid "Custom Handle Reference"
msgstr "Custom Handle Reference 自定义手柄参考"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:157
msgid ""
"B-Bones can use custom bones as their reference bone handles, instead of "
"only using the parent/child bones. To do so, enable the *Use Custom "
"Reference Handles* toggle in Pose Mode. If none are specified, then the "
"BBone will only use the Bendy Bone properties. When the option is on, "
"just use the specified bones instead of using trying looking at the "
"bone's neighbors."
msgstr ""
"样条骨（B-bones）可以使用自定义骨骼作为参考骨骼的手柄，而不是仅使用父/子骨骼。为此，在姿态模式下启用 *使用自定义参考手柄* "
"切换。如果没有指定，则样条骨（B-bones）将仅使用软骨骼（Bendy "
"Bone）属性。当选项打开时，只需使用指定的骨骼，而不是尝试查找骨骼的邻近。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:166
msgid "Relative"
msgstr "Relative  相对"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/bones/properties/bendy_bones.rst:163
msgid ""
"Instead of using the endpoints of the bones as absolute points in 3D "
"space it computes how far the reference bone has moved away from its rest"
" pose. The delta transformation is then applied as to the bone's own "
"endpoints to get the handle locations. This is useful if the custom "
"control bone is far away from its target."
msgstr ""
"不用使用骨骼的端点作为3D空间中的绝对点，它可以计算参考骨骼远离其重置姿势的距离。 "
"然后对骨骼自己的端点应用增量变换以获取手柄位置。这是有用的，如果自定义控制骨远离其目标。"

